(52, 1, 'Workplace', '<p>Every year a significant amount of productive business time is lost as a result of workplace injuries.  Even in a seemingly safe environment such as an office or call centre, people who spend a significant amount of time sitting at a desk or using a computer are at risk from a variety of common complaints and potential injuries.</p>\r\n<p>Many of us have suffered from problems such as back pain, headaches, fatigue or stress, which reduces performance at work.  In contrast, employees who are healthy and well are likely to be more productive. For example, a recent study by Medibank Private found that:<br />•	Healthy employees are nearly three times more productive than unhealthy employees<br />•	Unhealthy employees take up to nine times more sick leave than their healthy colleagues<br />•	Poor employee health and absenteeism costs Australian businesses $7 billion a year<br />For more statistics from the Medibank Private study or for more articles on workplace health, click on Workplace Health Articles below.</p>\r\n<p>Employers continue to look for new ways to help their staff avoid or mitigate these problems, as they are aware of the beneficial impact this has upon employee welfare, engagement and productivity.  The My 5 program is an ideal way to invest in the health and wellness of your employees.</p>\r\n<p>The program has been designed with corporate use specifically in mind.  The program is entirely web-based, allowing it to be rapidly deployed in your workplace, with no installation required.&#160; In addition, My 5 offers employers customised reporting and expert assistance with the analysis and interpretation of reports on the health and wellness of your workforce.&#160; </p>', 6, '2011-09-27 11:05:17', '2012-03-15 04:54:18'),
(53, 16, 'Body', '<p>Every year a significant amount of productive business time is lost as a result of workplace injuries.  Even in a seemingly safe environment such as an office or call centre, people who spend a significant amount of time sitting at a desk or using a computer are at risk from a variety of common complaints and potential injuries.</p>\r\n<p>Many of us have suffered from problems such as back pain, headaches, fatigue or stress, which reduces performance at work.  In contrast, employees who are healthy and well are likely to be more productive. For example, a recent study by Medibank Private found that:</p>\r\n<p>•	Healthy employees are nearly three times more productive than unhealthy employees<br />•	Unhealthy employees take up to nine times more sick leave than their healthy colleagues<br />•	Poor employee health and absenteeism costs Australian businesses $7 billion a year</p>\r\n<p>Employers continue to look for new ways to help their staff avoid or mitigate these problems, as they are aware of the beneficial impact this has upon employee welfare, engagement and productivity.  The My 5 program is an ideal way to invest in the health and wellness of your employees.</p>\r\n<p>The program has been designed with corporate use specifically in mind.  The program is entirely web-based, allowing it to be rapidly deployed in your workplace, with no installation required.&#160; In addition, My 5 offers employers customised reporting and expert assistance with the analysis and interpretation of reports on the health and wellness of your workforce. </p>', 0, '2011-09-27 11:10:14', '2012-03-04 10:04:04'),
(54, 16, 'Side Body', '', 1, '2011-09-27 11:10:14', '2012-03-04 10:04:04'),
(57, 18, 'Body', '<h3>My 5 offers the individual user a 12 month membership which gives you:</h3>\r\n<ul><li>Full access to all of the content in My 5 online</li>\r\n<li>The ability to use My 5 anywhere you can connect to the internet</li>\r\n<li>This includes mobile devices such as the iPad and Galaxy Tab</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>My 5 has been carefully designed to:</h3>\r\n<ul><li>Help to prevent and alleviate many of the pains and typical health issues commonly associated with long term computer usage</li>\r\n<li>Be easy and enjoyable to use</li>\r\n<li>Help to improve concentration and reduce stress</li>\r\n<li>Help you to keep track of your progress and general wellbeing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>So whether you use your computer for work, study or regularly at home, My 5 offers you an effective wellbeing program that can help you be happier, healthier and more productive.</p>\r\n<p><a href="/customers/sign_up" class="button">Start free 10 day trial</a>\r\n</p>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:04:05', '2012-03-05 05:33:08'),
(58, 18, 'Side Body', '', 1, '2011-10-07 05:04:05', '2012-03-05 05:33:08'),
(59, 19, 'Body', '<h3>My 5 offers Corporate users:</h3>\r\n<ul><li>Multi-user licensing</li>\r\n<li>Significant discounts for more than 100 users</li>\r\n<li>My 5 is entirely web based, and can be rapidly deployed with no installation needed. This allows your employees to access My 5 Online at work, home or anywhere they can connect to the internet.</li>\r\n<li>My 5 allows you the opportunity to co-brand, and gives you the ability to link with and complement any existing workplace wellbeing initiative you are currently offering your employees.</li>\r\n<li>In depth customisable reporting and expert assistance with interpretation of the findings, giving your business valuable information about the health and engagement levels of your work force.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>My 5 Enterprise packages offers users:</h3>\r\n<p>All of the benefits of the Corporate package, with innovative and effective extras including:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Tailored workshops such as Stretching and Posture/Stress Management/Emotional awareness and management.</li>\r\n<li>Train the trainer support, to help your team stay motivated and get the maximum benefits from the My 5 program</li>\r\n<li>Workplace massages customised to suit your needs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><br />Please <a title="Contact Us" href="/home/contact-us" class="green">click here</a> to contact us for further information and to arrange a discussion about your organisation''s particular needs\r\n\r\n</h3>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:04:20', '2011-12-02 01:46:53'),
(60, 19, 'Side Body', '', 1, '2011-10-07 05:04:20', '2011-12-02 01:46:53'),
(63, 21, 'Body', '<p><img src="/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI5MjAxMS8xMC8yNS8xMF8xMV8zMF80NzBfYWJvdXRfbXk1X3ZhbHVlc19jcm9wcGVkLmpwZwY6BkVU/about_my5_values_cropped.jpg" title="About My5 Values Cropped" alt="About My5 Values Cropped" rel="225x255" width="308" height="505" /></p>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:04:50', '2012-03-01 09:18:20'),
(65, 22, 'Body', '<p><img src="/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI2MjAxMS8xMC8yMS8xMl8yOF8xNV83OTRfcGVvcGxlX3BhZ2VfMl9jcm9wcGVkLmpwZwY6BkVU/people_page_2_cropped.jpg" title="People Page 2 Cropped" alt="People Page 2 Cropped" rel="225x255" width="308" height="505" /></p>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:05:09', '2011-10-24 23:11:53'),
(67, 23, 'Body', '<h2>My 5 was founded by Tim Norris, an internationally accredited practitioner who has 20 years experience in the fields of natural health and fitness.</h2>\r\n<p>Tim worked in one of the UK''s leading health clubs as a personal trainer and Pilates teacher for over 7 years.  His year as a health consultant and bodywork practitioner at the BBC in 2003 inspired him to continue his work in the corporate workplace to enhance computer users'' wellbeing. </p>\r\n<p>Tim became aware of the need to address more effectively the typical complaints and issues that presented within a workplace.  Together with a number of highly qualified and experienced practitioners, he has been able to structure and develop the My 5 program to significantly alleviate the aches and pains commonly associated with extended computer usage.</p>\r\n<p>Tim''s experience in the corporate workplace is supported by extensive training and qualifications in a range of natural health modalities, including:</p>\r\n<ul><li>    Fitness consultant</li>\r\n<li>Sports therapy, rehabilitation and massage</li>\r\n<li>Pilates</li>\r\n<li>Acupuncture</li>\r\n<li>Bowen technique</li>\r\n<li>Kinesiology</li>\r\n<li>Bio-energetics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="font-style: italic;">"I’m passionate about helping people to learn more about what causes their day to day health and wellness problems.  By inspiring people to understand their body’s needs better, I can empower them to take more responsibility for their own wellbeing.  I see the My 5 software program as one of the ways I can achieve this." </p>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:05:29', '2011-12-02 01:50:12'),
(68, 23, 'Side Body', '', 1, '2011-10-07 05:05:29', '2011-12-02 01:50:12'),
(69, 24, 'Body', '<h2>Stephanie Campanale, Key Media</h2>\r\n<p>It was our pleasure to work with Tim Norris of My 5 at the National HR Summit 2012. Tim led our audience of 300+ delegates in a series of exercises to “wake up” and energize them during the day of presentations. The audience enjoyed the stretches and realised that these techniques are easy to implement and would improve their team’s performance during the daily work day. </p>\r\n<p>The My 5 techniques strengthen healthy workplace strategies and practices. </p>\r\n<h2>QBE LMI</h2>\r\n<p>Tim recently facilitated a one hour workshop for employees across a number states. The workshop covered a range of specific stretches and postural exercises for the workplace environment that can help improve posture and release muscular tension. Our employees found the workshop very practical with many really enjoying the opportunity to practise what they''ve learnt. I''ve seen many of the posters Tim provided hanging around the office and people were really keen to practice their stretches. Thanks Tim for a great practical workshop!</p>\r\n<h2>CMC Markets Asia Pacific</h2>\r\n<p>I thought his approach, techniques and teaching methods were great - very clear and precise. Tim always kept in mind that we are in an office environment and the stretches he showed us were appropriate. He also showed us some that as he mentioned should be done at home. Tim came around and made sure we were all doing the particular movements correctly as to not harm ourselves. The cards and posters he left us to put around the office and to take away and to keep reminding us were great too. If anyone had any questions I thought that he answered them with a lot of fact and satisfied the person asking the question and also made further suggestions to assist in particular parts of the body that were causing problems.</p>\r\n<h2>Christine Ammann, Kinesiologist, SA</h2>\r\n<p>I love the My5 program as it incorporates a quick fix for everyone at any time, combining five very powerful modalities that work extremely well together.  When doing my administration work I often spend long periods of time sitting in front of my computer or marking assignments, and I guess, like most people, forget to take a break every so often.  By the end of the day of course, I end up with sore shoulder and neck muscles and weary eyes!  Having the program loaded onto my computer with the timely reminder set - I can relax and focus on my work until I am told what to do!  Being able to choose from different techniques without much fuss is great and improves my productivity - plus I still have enough energy left at the end of the day to spend time with my family without being tired, grumpy or sore - laugh!</p>\r\n<h2>Angela Stott, La Source International</h2>\r\n<p>When looking at options where we wanted to not only retain our staff but also promote well being in the work place, we were finding it a challenge to find a concept that would really work without taking up too much employee time.  Once we signed up to the program, we were instantly impressed with the ease of functionality of the program, the appeal to our employees and also the sheer professionalism of it all.  It is a seamless journey for the user and a valuable tool for any company looking to invest that little extra in their team.</p>\r\n<h2>Mimi Fong, Amicas Global&#160;</h2>\r\n<p>My 5 impressed me with its innovative yet simple approach to wellness in the workplace. It takes the basic principle of " Healthier employees equals greater productivity levels" and transforms this into easy to follow exercises which can be done anywhere in the workplace. My 5 has made a tangible difference to my business particularly in boosting concentration and alertness levels throughout the day. It is a must for any organisation serious in their commitment towards maintaining and enhancing the health and wellbeing of their most valuable assets - their employees.</p>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:05:44', '2012-05-06 23:57:08'),
(70, 24, 'Side Body', '', 1, '2011-10-07 05:05:44', '2012-05-06 23:57:08'),
(71, 25, 'Body', '<h2>The My 5 team is growing! </h2>\n<p>We are often on the look out for motivated, energetic and dedicated people to join our team.&#160; Watch this space for upcoming positions.</p>\n<p>We offer employees the opportunity to work in a dynamic and respectful environment. We are committed to helping each member of our team reach their full potential. Importantly, My 5 supports the commitment of its employees to the community.</p>\n<p>If you are interested, please <a title="Contact Us" href="/home/contact-us">drop us a line</a>.</p>', 0, '2011-10-07 05:06:02', '2011-10-11 21:19:52'),
